,Recommended,268220,28351073,"Posted: 13 December, 2016",all,Dek,"Fantastic game, was looking for something for my fiancée and me to play as couch co-op. A rare gem that has full controller support, shared-screen co-op, as well as online co-op that's balanced on its own, and is different enough from the regular game mode to make it worth the play through, not just ""oh here's the same game but with two people now."" Good fast-paced arcade-y action that's a lot of fun to play.The game mechanics are pretty easy to pick up, it's challenging enough to keep you frustrated at times but with strategy and upgrades you work out the best strategy to beat every type of enemy. That's probably the game's strongest part, that almost every enemy (or combination of enemies) no matter how weak it might seem, has the ability to ♥♥♥♥ up your day. What might seem like a nuisance at the start of the game becomes a swarm of holy♥♥♥♥♥♥by level 30. The game devs have definitely done their jobs doing playthroughs and testing to make sure it's got a good balance between easy-enough-to-not♥♥♥♥♥♥you-off and hard-enough-to-make-beating-a-boss-feel-rewarding.Levels are great, there are random props and mood that sets the backdrop and gives a decent immersion. Randomly-generated keeps it pretty new every time, and each third of the game has a slightly different style which is nice and keeps things fresh. The music is also fantastic, plenty of dubs and wubs that match the sci-fi action feel of the game, and was an awesome way to pump you up while playing. Cycles through different sets of tracks for different levels, great addition to play.The only thing keeping this game from being ""THE BEST EVER"" is a larger story that kind of ties the game together...there's a bit of lip-service to the robots on a space station malfunctioning and you having to clear them out, blah blah blah...it's all the game *needs* but to make it a best-of contender it would be cool to know more about Zed. He seems like a cool guy."
