76561197998485563,Not Recommended,268220,20951187,"Posted: 4 February, 2016",all,Habilis,"I was hoping to scratch that ARPG itch with this game and it simply came up short.  A Bastion clone it is not.While there are a variety of enemies and guns, I felt the core gameplay to be fickle and problematic:1) The aiming does not feel precise.  Often times you will end up shooting next to a foe when you are clicking right on them - use of a controller makes this actually even worse.  The game is meant to be played with auto-aim and this often takes the satisfaction out of a game like this.2) The biggest problem in the game is that it feels like you are fighting the controls.  You are locked into an animation once you start it which is significantly more cumbersome than it is challenging.  For example, you cannot go from melee to shooting or rolling to anything in a reasonable time frame -- you will have to wait for your character to finish said action, delay and then start your new action.3) The game relies on grind rather than content.  Making an area too difficult to complete so you have to re-do previous areas is not a good stand in for content -- it just shows you purposely undertune the starting options.  What necessarily comes with this is an inverse difficulty curve - easy at the end and hard at the outset.The core issue comes down to gameplay.  At its heart the game feels unresponsive and slow -- you will not die because you couldn't react in time, but because the game locks you into animation lag. And this is coming from a Monster Hunter veteran, I am no stranger to animation lag and meaningful gameplay."
